A crash left two men critically injured today morning. AT around 6:45am, the Netcare 911 responded to reports of a collision on the Western Bypass of Sandton. The ER24 Media Liaison Officer, Shawn Herbst said reports from the scene indicate that two vehicles were involved in a collision resulting in one of the vehicles catching alight and burning out completely. “Paramedics assessed the scene and found that the drivers of the cars both adult males sustained serious injuries and required Advanced Life Support intervention to stabilize them. “Once treated the patients were transported by ambulance to hospital for further treatment,” said Herbst.  